'''Thomas Herpich''' (born October 1979) is an [[Americans|American]] artist who is best known for being a writer and storyboard artist on the animated television series ''[[Adventure Time]]''.

==History==
Herpich graduated from the [[School of Visual Arts]] (SVA), and was known in [[Alternative comics|indie cartooning]] circles before he was hired to work on ''Adventure Time''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Arsenault|first=Marc|title=Meet The Artists of Adventure Time|url=http://wowcool.com/engine/meet-the-artists-of-adventure-time|publisher=WowCool|accessdate=April 27, 2014|date=October 11, 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305083822/http://wowcool.com/engine/meet-the-artists-of-adventure-time|archivedate=March 5, 2014|df=}}</ref> He was eventually hired on as a prop and character designer for the [[Adventure Time (season 1)|first season]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Herpich|first=Thomas|title=Adventure Time|url=http://herpich.blogspot.com/2009/02/adventure-time.html|publisher=[[Blogspot]]|accessdate=April 27, 2014|date=February 9, 2009}}</ref> before storyboarding the season one episode "Freak City" and being promoted to storyboard artist in [[Adventure Time (season 2)|season two]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Herpich|first=Thomas|title=Storytelling|url=http://herpich.blogspot.com/2010/11/story-telling.html|publisher=[[Blogspot]]|accessdate=April 27, 2014|date=November 5, 2010}}</ref>

==Accolades==
Tom Herpich's work on ''Adventure Time'' has gained him two Outstanding Individual Achievement in Animation Emmy Award wins, along with three [[Primetime Emmy Award for Short-format Animation]] nominations: he was first nominated for the [[Adventure Time (season 3)|third-season]] episode "Too Young" in 2012, along with his then-storyboarding partner [[Jesse Moynihan]]; he was later nominated for the [[Adventure Time (season 5)|fifth-season]] episode "[[Be More (Adventure Time)|Be More]]", along with his partner Steve Wolfhard; and in 2016 he was nominated for his solo work on the [[Adventure Time (season 7)|seventh-season]] episode "[[The Hall of Egress]]".<ref name="emmyssitearchive">{{cite web|title=Adventure Time|url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/adventure-time|work=''Emmys.com''|publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]|accessdate=January 23, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.emmys.com/sites/default/files/Downloads/66th-nominations-list.pdf | title=66th Emmy Nomination List | accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Lewis|first1=Dave|title=Complete List of 2016 Emmy Nominees|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-emmys-2016-nominees-winners-list-20160714-snap-story.html|website=[[The Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=July 14, 2016|date=July 14, 2016}}</ref> In both 2015 and 2016, he was awarded an Outstanding Individual Achievement in Animation Emmy for his work on the episodes "[[Walnuts & Rain]]" and "[[Stakes (miniseries)|''Stakes'' Part 8: The Dark Cloud]]".<ref>{{cite web|title=Juried Award Winners Announced for the 67th Emmy Awards|url=http://www.emmys.com/news/awards-news/juried-award-winners-announced-67th-emmy-awards|accessdate=September 11, 2015|date=September 10, 2015|work=''Emmys.com''|publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]}}</ref><ref name="yahooemmy">{{cite web|last1=Yahoo TV staff|title=Emmys 2016: ‘Adventure Time,’ ‘Robot Chicken’ Among First Winners|url=https://www.yahoo.com/tv/emmys-animation-awards-adventure-time-000000538.html|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|accessdate=August 26, 2016|date=August 26, 2016}}</ref> Furthermore, his solo storyboarded episode "Thank You" was screened at the [[Sundance Film Festival]], was nominated for a Best Animated Special Production [[Annie Award]], and was nearly nominated for an [[Academy Awards|Oscar Award]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Thank You&nbsp;– Festival Program|url=http://filmguide.sundance.org/film/13180/thank_you|work=''Sundance.org''|publisher=[[Sundance Institute]]|accessdate=January 23, 2013}}</ref><ref name=annie2011>{{cite web|last=Beck|first=Jerry|title=Annie Award Nominations 2011|url=http://www.cartoonbrew.com/events/annie-award-nominations-2011-53561.html|publisher=Cartoon Brew LLC|work=[[Cartoon Brew]]|accessdate=January 23, 2013|date=December 5, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title='Thank You' Backgrounds|url=http://pancakeshio.tumblr.com/post/13608212119/adventuretime-thank-you-backgrounds-the-sad|publisher=[[Frederator Studios]]|accessdate=February 3, 2013|year=2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130217003818/http://pancakeshio.tumblr.com/post/13608212119/adventuretime-thank-you-backgrounds-the-sad|archivedate=February 17, 2013|df=}}</ref>

